Text: Built-in Data-Packet Loss Detector smart part
Can stop or enable the fuel flow between two tanks or between a tank and an engine. Control it by action group or context menu. Use this to control your CoM.
Can be used to control the fuel flow of fuel lines. Attach this to the source tank and attach a fuel line to it. Turn it on and off via the right click menu or action groups. Off by default.
ALT-Pro Altimeter and Action Group Trigger
Fires an event if the vessel reaches the specified height.
Comm-Pro Communication Net Action Group Trigger
Fires an event if the vessel loses or gains Commnet connectivity
Fires an event if the Electric Charge of the whole craft has drained below or been increased above the defined threshold.
Drainex 1 - Fuel Sensor and Action Group Trigger
Fires an event if the tank or battery it is attached to has drained. Works with any resource.
Fires an event if the sensor detects another craft with a proximity sensor on the same channel
Radio-GAGA - A Radio for Action Groups

Transmits and receives commands between radios on the same channel for all vessels in rendering range (approx 2000m). It can set the heading of receiving vessels to the heading of the active vessel. It can also keep the headings synchronized (Sync. Head.).

Fires an event if a specified resource of the whole craft has drained below the defined threshold.  Also, this can be set to fire an event if the specified resource of the whole craft has been filled above a defined threshold.
Speed-Pro Speedometer and Action Group Trigger
Fires an event if the vessel reaches the specified speed.
Fires an event after the specified time has elapsed. Activate this device with an action group.
Use this valve to dump excess fuel before re-entry. The valve dumps the resources contained in the tank it is attached to.
Use this valve to dump excess fuel before re-entry. Straight fuel dump. The valve dumps the resources contained in the tank it is attached to.
OBT-Pro Orbit and Action Group Trigger
Fires an event if the vessel reaches the specified orbital element.
Fires an event when the attached SRB's thrust drops to less than or equal to its mass
